The paper deals with counting independent sets and kernels of regular graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of binary decision diagrams suggests a focus on algorithms and complexity theory (cs.IT). The Bethe approximation and the analysis of fluctuations in the logarithm of the counts suggest a connection to statistical physics and information theory (cs.CC, cs.SI). Finally, the study of regular graphs and their properties suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
